Days 1-30: rank SWOT items by impact and controllability, choose the top two strengths to exploit, top two weaknesses to remediate, top two opportunities to pursue, and top two threats to mitigate, then assign owners, budgets, milestones, and KPIs. Days 31-60: run pilots that use strengths against the best opportunities, execute corrective work on key weaknesses, and deploy risk controls for priority threats. Days 61-90: scale pilots that meet KPI thresholds, stop or redesign those that do not, institutionalize successful process fixes, and refresh the SWOT based on measured results.
